### Multilingual Bridge API Tests
### Requires VS Code REST Client extension
### Run each request by clicking "Send Request" above it

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

###

### Get All Supported Languages
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/translate/languages

###

### Detect Language - Hindi
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/translate/detect-language
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "नमस्ते, आप कैसे हैं?"
}

###

### Detect Language - Telugu
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/translate/detect-language
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "మీరు ఎలా ఉన్నారు?"
}

###

### Translate English → Hindi
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/translate/translate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "Hello, how are you? I hope you are doing well today.",
  "source_lang": "en",
  "target_lang": "hi"
}

###

### Translate Hindi → Telugu
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/translate/translate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "नमस्ते, मेरा नाम राज है।",
  "source_lang": "hi",
  "target_lang": "te"
}

###

### Paste & Reply - Explain (with slang)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/paste-reply/explain
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pasted_text": "r u cumin 2day? gr8! brb 😊",
  "user_native_lang": "hi",
  "speed": "slow"
}

###

### Paste & Reply - Explain Hindi message
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/paste-reply/explain
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pasted_text": "कल मीटिंग है सुबह 10 बजे, देर मत करना",
  "user_native_lang": "te",
  "speed": "slow"
}

###

